<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-03-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-03-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1630" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1630">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 353.117R33/1.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American Consul at St.
                                    Michael’s</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 345.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-27">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1913</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your despatch
                            No. 765 of February 27, 1913, concerning the action of the officials in
                            the Azores, especially in the district of Horta, in requiring military
                            service, or imposing fines in lieu thereof, in cases of persons born in
                            the Azores whose fathers, also natives of the Azores, had previously
                            obtained naturalization as citizens of the United States.</p>
                        <p>I enclose herewith, for your information, a copy of an instruction of
                            this day to the Legation at Lisbon concerning the matter.<note n="2" xml:id="d1630fn2">See the next paper.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For <signed>Mr. Adee, Acting Secretary</signed>: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>